<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Birth" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Birth,</orth> 1) the act of coming into life: <cit><quote>truer stars did govern Proteus' b.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 7, 74</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.521" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 521</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 40</bibl> etc. Plur. <cit><quote>births:</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 118</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.215" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 215</bibl> (Ff <emph>birth</emph>).<lb />2) the act of bringing forth: <cit><quote>two children at one b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.147" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 147</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>both at a b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 212</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a grievous burthen was thy b. to me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.167" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 167</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>am I a mother to the b. of three?</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.369" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 369</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) that which is born: <cit><quote>a dearer b. than this his love had brought,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 32.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 32, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.230" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 230</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.215" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 215</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.104" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 104</bibl> etc. Plur. <cit><quote>births:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.122" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 122</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 35</bibl>.
<lb />4) extraction, descent: <cit><quote>some glory in their b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 91.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 91, 1</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.37.5" default="NO" valid="yes">37, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.76.8" default="NO" valid="yes">76, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 4, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.172" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 7, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 20.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.73" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.61" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.152" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.120" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.5.15" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 15</bibl> <emph>(--s)</emph> etc. <emph>a match of b.</emph> == a high-born match, <bibl n="shak. jn 2.430" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 430</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>